# Tokhoy, Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Tokhoy () is a rural locality (an ulus) in Selenginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 2,819 as of 2010. There are 68 streets.
Geography
Tokhoy is located 13&nbsp;km northeast of Gusinoozyorsk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Zhargalanta is the nearest rural locality.
